<h3>New Pet Skill</h3>
<p>Air now casts a damage-dealing stun.&nbsp; Like Earth, the damage done by
stun is 10 + pet level.</p>
<p>I've got no proof of it, but I believe that magician summoned focus items
help.&nbsp; Give the pet a bracer and ring and it should cast faster and for
more damage.&nbsp; However, since log data does not show pet spell damage, I
can't be certain this is actually helpful.</p>
<p>Note: The Broom of Trillion will not benefit pets over the 49th summon.&nbsp;
Only the Staff of Elemental Mastery: Air will act as a focus item on this and the
59 air pet.</p>

<h3>Boon of Immolation</h3>
<p>This is a group version of the level 49 damage shield (25 point DS and fire
resist).&nbsp; Note two important things about this spell:<br>

<br>
1) it costs three times the mana of the level 49 spell, but it lasts roughly 2.5
times as long<br>
2) it will not DS your pet - pets only benefit from single target spells, not
group buffs</p>

<p>You should use Boon instead of single target if you are DSing more than 1
player tank in your group.&nbsp; Sometimes I use it even if there is only one
main tank just for the longer buff (and I can see when it wears off).</p>

<p>Note: Since Magician DS do more damage than any player-cast DS, magician DS
will overwrite most other player-cast DS (subject to level).&nbsp; This is
usually (but not always) ideal.&nbsp; Rangers, for example have a self buff at
high level that is a weak DS that also buffs the ranger.&nbsp; They won't be
happy if you kill their buff by casting your group DS.&nbsp; (Trust me, I've
sent many a ranger to a therapist).&nbsp; If you want to cast the group DS, I
suggest you ask your group before the first cast.</p>

<h3>Quiver of Marr</h3>
<p>This summon results in a quiver and 6 sets of 20 arrows.&nbsp; The quiver has a modifier on it that will enable its 
user to fire arrows at a faster than normal rate.&nbsp; </p>
<p><i>Historical Note: Due to a coding limitation, the arrows would originally not auto-load.&nbsp; That is, once the 
first stack of 20 arrows has been used up, the player will have to manually drop the next batch of 20 into the ammo 
slot.</i></p>
<p><i>Tech Note: I believe the failure to auto load was the result of each stack having a unique item number.&nbsp; For 
auto load to work, additional ammo must have the same item number.&nbsp; Why does each stack have different item numbers 
when they all have the same stats?&nbsp; Your cursor could not be loaded with
multiple items of the same id.&nbsp; Again, this is my speculation.&nbsp; Verant
hasn't made an official statement to my knowledge.&nbsp; Regardless, it's 
working fine now.&nbsp; Two years after the spell came into the game.</i></p>
